\newlabel{fig:gains}{{9}{13}{Gain decomposition: where do extra converged samples come from? \textbf {Left (LJ):} the 50k step budget provides modest gains; kicks add very little ($+$0.7\,pts at $n{=}2.0$). \textbf {Right (DFTB0):} both 50k steps and kicks provide substantial gains, especially at high noise ($+$12.2\,pts from kicks at $n{=}2.0$)}{figure.9}{}}
